to the editor re harvard adopts new rules for early admission applicants news article april 11 early admissions was conceived as a device to lock in the admission of students with outstanding potential now it is simply a what have i got to lose philosophy for ambitious students who begin their college shopping early college admissions officers find themselves with a workload that has just about doubled given the pressure to occupy one of those coveted ivy league seats would n't it be simplest and fairest to eliminate early admissions giving students just one shot at the prize and thereby treating all applicants equally vita c tauss plandome ny april 11 2003

